{
  "text": "Cancer is multifactorial disease and major health problem worldwide. The alteration of molecular/genetic pathways plays role in the development and progression of cancer. The treatment module based on allopathic is effective on one side but also shows adverse effect on the normal cell. In contrast, studies showed that some methoxylated flavonoids from D. kotschyi such as xanthomicrol [CITATION_1] and calycopterin [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] have safe and great anticancer properties [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . The leaf extract of D. kotschyi showed a higher cytotoxic effect against A172, A2780-s, HL60, KB, K562, MCF-7, Saos-2, Hela, A2780-cp, A549, A375, and HFFF-P16 cell lines [CITATION_7] , while Faham et al. [CITATION_8] reported calycopterin inhibition of proliferation of lymphocyte in a dose-dependent manner (IC50 = 1.7 g/mL); Moghaddam et al. [CITATION_9] isolated eight flavonoid aglycones (luteolin, naringenin, apigenin, isokaempferide, cirsimaritin, penduletin, xanthomicrol, and calycopterin) from the aerial parts of D. kotschyi and reported that they had anticancer activities.",
  "correct_citation": {
